        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer77446919" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10312852394704245696">Had to read this for a first year university thing, and greatly resented this first uni experience. What I got out of this book was that, basically, if you weren&apos;t helping the sick in Haiti, then you suck. I felt like Tracy Kidder didn&apos;t appreciate the valuable work of anyone else in any other field - or, honestly, anybody but Dr. Farmer. Then Dr. Farmer came to speak to my school, and I hated the book even more after being forced to listen to him. I rarely hate books, but Kidder&apos;s uncritical pr</span>
  <span id="freeText10312852394704245696" style="display:none">Had to read this for a first year university thing, and greatly resented this first uni experience. What I got out of this book was that, basically, if you weren't helping the sick in Haiti, then you suck. I felt like Tracy Kidder didn't appreciate the valuable work of anyone else in any other field - or, honestly, anybody but Dr. Farmer. Then Dr. Farmer came to speak to my school, and I hated the book even more after being forced to listen to him. I rarely hate books, but Kidder's uncritical praise of Farmer made me see Farmer as an egotistical jackass. Helpful in the grand scheme of things, sure, but I don't want to hear about him. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10312852394704245696" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
